    "There is a distinction in the literature between clinical and biomedical texts and they are understood to be different in terms of their linguistic qualities (Alsentzer et al. 2019).",
    "Clinical notes are collected by healthcare professionals when the patient is seen or being treated.",
    "They are free-text, without a fixed structure, can contain spelling errors, abbreviations, non-standard grammar, differences in personal style and words and phrases from different languages.",
    "These characteristics contribute to the fact that they are still underutilised as a resource (Sanyal, Rubin, and Banerjee 2022).",
    "What is referred to as biomedical texts, on the other hand, are often compilations of scientific texts in the biomedical and life sciences from resources such as PubMed."
